Class ElementFactory<T extends DataElement>

java.lang.Object
au.edu.anu.twcore.ecosystem.runtime.system.ElementFactory<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
Categorized<T>, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Factory<T>, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Singleton<T>
Direct Known Subclasses:
ArenaFactory, ComponentFactory, GroupFactory, LifeCycleFactory
public abstract class ElementFactory<T extends DataElement> extends Object implements fr.ens.biologie.generic.Factory<T>, Categorized<T>, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Singleton<T>
A factory for any system element type - ancestor to SystemFactory, LifeCycle factory, GroupFactory etc.

CAUTION: an element factory is conceptually 1..1 with an element type. When components must be instantiated, they are often associated with a container which has a 1..1 relation with an element type instance node (Group, LifeCycle, COmponent)., which have a 1..* relation with element type.

Author:
J. Gignoux - 23 avr. 2020
